### GIT ESSENTIAL COMMANDS AND USAGE

git add filename-  adding file to git repo

git config --global user.email "you@example.com".   --- to let git know about user details
git config --global user.name "Your Name"


git commit -m "added newfile"   commiting changes with comment

git branch my1stbranch. || git branch - creating new branch and checking what branches we have

git checkout my1stbranch- switch to new branch from active branch 

echo 'Here is some text in my newfile.' >> newfile -- adding data into file

git status- to check commits on our branches

git log- to get history of recent commits

git revert HEAD --no-edit-  to revert back from last commit

git merge my1stbranch- merging branches to master





cloning and forking:

git clone
git branch feature-add-color
git checkout feature-add-color
git add . - adds all untracked files into staging area
git commit -sm 'adding red color feature'
git checkout main && git merge feature-add-color
git push origin main
create pull requets for approval

